org.kitesdk.data

Class DatasetDescriptor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.kitesdk.data.DatasetDescriptor

  • @Immutable
public class DatasetDescriptor
extends Object

    The structural definition of a Dataset.

    Each Dataset has an associated Schema and optional PartitionStrategy defined at the time of creation. You use instances of this class to hold this information. You are strongly encouraged to use the inner DatasetDescriptor.Builder to create new instances.

    • Method Detail

      • getSchema

        public Schema getSchema()
        Get the associated Schema. Depending on the underlying storage system, this schema can be simple (that is, records made up of only scalar types) or complex (that is, containing other records, lists, and so on). Validation of the supported schemas is performed by the managing repository, not the dataset or descriptor itself.
        Returns:
        the schema

      • getSchemaUrl

        @Nullable
public URL getSchemaUrl()
        Get a URL from which the Schema can be retrieved (optional). This method might return null if the schema is not stored at a persistent URL (for example, if it were constructed from a literal string).
